<b>Publishing Guidelines</b>

Articles submitted to <BLINK><font size="3"><font color=DarkCyan><i><b>e-artDocuments</font size="3"></font color=DarkCyan> </BLINK></b></i> must be accompanied by a covering letter that states the title, the author and the section in which the document is intended for inclusion. Articles will be reviewed for publication by the Editorial Board and two external reviewers. The external reviewers will be selected unanimously by the journal to evaluate the content and methodology of submissions. Submitting authors may request a summary of the reports provided by the reviewers, which will indicate how to remedy deficiencies or make requested changes. 

<u>1) Article:</u> 
Articles must be no longer than 25 pages; reviews must be between 2 and 4 pages in length. If an author wishes to exceed these limits, he or she should contact the journal <BLINK><font size="3"><font color=DarkCyan><i><b>e-artDocuments</font size="3"></font color=DarkCyan> </BLINK></b></i> prior to submission. For online submissions, articles in Word and Open Office are preferred.  

<u>2) Title:</u>
